interprets the device status as a result.\n\n\n**Confirming the Wake Architecture**\n\nI\u0027ve confirmed the \"blank ping\" solution. It silences error noise in Go, allowing the Wake Cron task a clean run. The user\u0027s \"dummy IP\" strategy is brilliant. UpSnap\u0027s shared Cron execution likely choked on constant ping failures. Now, using a \"dummy IP\" and \"shadow command\" results in a perfect \"IP as a switch\" logic, completing the architecture.\n\n\n",
